{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MTCDTZ6ccakjTUvsbbCjBt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"One test failed: \"returns null when |z-score| == threshold (strict <)\". Let me check the code:\n\n```js\nif (Math.abs(zScore) < this.zScoreThreshold) return null;\n```\n\nSo when `|zScore| == threshold`, the condition is `false` (not less than), so it does NOT return null — it proceeds to generate a signal. My test was wrong — I assumed it was strict `<` but the behavior is that at exactly the threshold, a signal IS generated (since `1.5 < 1.5` is false).\n\n\nI need to update that test to reflect the actual behavior — when the z-score equals the threshold exactly, a signal gets generated, not null.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4655,"cache_read_input_tokens":26732,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4655},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5355c183-8c4f-4fd6-991f-0c1f62b62566","uuid":"c6c6b5a2-e5af-4640-b5c6-d202f8bf2372"}
