{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YZTUKpZZgMx4Z4sDL5wpei","type":"tool_result","content":"/**\n * Longshot Fading Strategy\n * Sells YES contracts priced 5¢-20¢ in niche categories\n * Based on UCD/GWU 2025 research on favorite-longshot bias\n * \n * Author: Dave (Full Stack Engineer)\n * Task: #220\n */\n\n\"use strict\";\n\n/**\n * LongshotFadingStrategy generates signals to sell overpriced longshots.\n * Research shows contracts priced 5¢-20¢ lose ~60% of invested capital\n * due to retail overpricing of tail-risk events.\n */\nclass LongshotFadingStrategy {\n  constructor(options = {}) {\n    this.name = \"LongshotFading\";\n    this.minPrice = options.minPrice || 5;    // Minimum YES price to consider\n    this.maxPrice = options.maxPrice || 20;   // Maximum YES price to consider\n    this.targetCategories = options.targetCategories || [\n      \"Weather\", \n      \"Entertainment\", \n      \"Culture\",\n      \"Geopolitics\"\n    ];\n    this.minConfidence = options.minConfidence || 0.7;\n    this.minEdge = options.minEdge || 2;\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Generate a signal for a single market\n   * @param {Object} market - Market data from Bob's API\n   * @returns {Object|null} Signal or null if no opportunity\n   */\n  generateSignal(market) {\n    // Filter by category\n    if (!this.targetCategories.includes(market.category)) {\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    const yesPrice = market.yes_mid || market.yesPrice || market.yesBid;\n    if (!yesPrice) return null;\n\n    // Check if price is in our target range (5¢-20¢)\n    if (yesPrice < this.minPrice || yesPrice > this.maxPrice) {\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    // Calculate edge based on favorite-longshot bias research\n    // Research shows 5-20¢ contracts are systematically overpriced\n    // Higher overpricing at lower prices\n    const overpricingFactor = (this.maxPrice - yesPrice) / (this.maxPrice - this.minPrice);\n    const expectedEdge = Math.min(yesPrice * 0.15 * overpricingFactor, 10);\n    \n    // Confidence based on price (lower price = higher confidence in overpricing)\n    const confidence = Math.min(this.minConfidence + (0.25 * overpricingFactor), 0.95);\n\n    // Skip if doesn't meet minimums\n    if (confidence < this.minConfidence || expectedEdge < this.minEdge) {\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    return {\n      marketId: market.id,\n      side: \"no\",  // Sell YES = buy NO (or sell YES directly if supported)\n      signalType: \"entry\",\n      confidence,\n      targetPrice: 100 - yesPrice,  // NO price\n      currentPrice: 100 - yesPrice,\n      expectedEdge: Math.round(expectedEdge),\n      recommendedContracts: 10,  // Will be overridden by PositionSizer\n      reason: `Longshot fade: YES=${yesPrice}¢ in ${market.category}. ` +\n        `Overpricing factor: ${overpricingFactor.toFixed(2)}. ` +\n        `Research: UCD/GWU 2025 favorite-longshot bias study.`,\n      metadata: {\n        strategy: this.name,\n        yesPrice,\n        category: market.category,\n        overpricingFactor,\n        researchBasis: \"UCD/GWU 2025 - favorite-longshot bias on Kalshi\"\n      }\n    };\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Batch generate signals for multiple markets\n   * @param {Array} markets - Array of market objects\n   * @returns {Array} Array of signals\n   */\n  generateSignals(markets) {\n    const signals = [];\n    for (const market of markets) {\n      const signal = this.generateSignal(market);\n      if (signal) {\n        signals.push(signal);\n      }\n    }\n    return signals.sort((a, b) => b.confidence - a.confidence);\n  }\n}\n\nmodule.exports = { LongshotFadingStrategy };","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cdc38eb2-8e84-4ba4-a86a-56104d2ecaf3","uuid":"9c8a5529-72b0-4f30-b227-2f9b809f9c81","timestamp":"2026-04-03T23:25:57.032Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"/**\n * Longshot Fading Strategy\n * Sells YES contracts priced 5¢-20¢ in niche categories\n * Based on UCD/GWU 2025 research on favorite-longshot bias\n * \n * Author: Dave (Full Stack Engineer)\n * Task: #220\n */\n\n\"use strict\";\n\n/**\n * LongshotFadingStrategy generates signals to sell overpriced longshots.\n * Research shows contracts priced 5¢-20¢ lose ~60% of invested capital\n * due to retail overpricing of tail-risk events.\n */\nclass LongshotFadingStrategy {\n  constructor(options = {}) {\n    this.name = \"LongshotFading\";\n    this.minPrice = options.minPrice || 5;    // Minimum YES price to consider\n    this.maxPrice = options.maxPrice || 20;   // Maximum YES price to consider\n    this.targetCategories = options.targetCategories || [\n      \"Weather\", \n      \"Entertainment\", \n      \"Culture\",\n      \"Geopolitics\"\n    ];\n    this.minConfidence = options.minConfidence || 0.7;\n    this.minEdge = options.minEdge || 2;\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Generate a signal for a single market\n   * @param {Object} market - Market data from Bob's API\n   * @returns {Object|null} Signal or null if no opportunity\n   */\n  generateSignal(market) {\n    // Filter by category\n    if (!this.targetCategories.includes(market.category)) {\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    const yesPrice = market.yes_mid || market.yesPrice || market.yesBid;\n    if (!yesPrice) return null;\n\n    // Check if price is in our target range (5¢-20¢)\n    if (yesPrice < this.minPrice || yesPrice > this.maxPrice) {\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    // Calculate edge based on favorite-longshot bias research\n    // Research shows 5-20¢ contracts are systematically overpriced\n    // Higher overpricing at lower prices\n    const overpricingFactor = (this.maxPrice - yesPrice) / (this.maxPrice - this.minPrice);\n    const expectedEdge = Math.min(yesPrice * 0.15 * overpricingFactor, 10);\n    \n    // Confidence based on price (lower price = higher confidence in overpricing)\n    const confidence = Math.min(this.minConfidence + (0.25 * overpricingFactor), 0.95);\n\n    // Skip if doesn't meet minimums\n    if (confidence < this.minConfidence || expectedEdge < this.minEdge) {\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    return {\n      marketId: market.id,\n      side: \"no\",  // Sell YES = buy NO (or sell YES directly if supported)\n      signalType: \"entry\",\n      confidence,\n      targetPrice: 100 - yesPrice,  // NO price\n      currentPrice: 100 - yesPrice,\n      expectedEdge: Math.round(expectedEdge),\n      recommendedContracts: 10,  // Will be overridden by PositionSizer\n      reason: `Longshot fade: YES=${yesPrice}¢ in ${market.category}. ` +\n        `Overpricing factor: ${overpricingFactor.toFixed(2)}. ` +\n        `Research: UCD/GWU 2025 favorite-longshot bias study.`,\n      metadata: {\n        strategy: this.name,\n        yesPrice,\n        category: market.category,\n        overpricingFactor,\n        researchBasis: \"UCD/GWU 2025 - favorite-longshot bias on Kalshi\"\n      }\n    };\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Batch generate signals for multiple markets\n   * @param {Array} markets - Array of market objects\n   * @returns {Array} Array of signals\n   */\n  generateSignals(markets) {\n    const signals = [];\n    for (const market of markets) {\n      const signal = this.generateSignal(market);\n      if (signal) {\n        signals.push(signal);\n      }\n    }\n    return signals.sort((a, b) => b.confidence - a.confidence);\n  }\n}\n\nmodule.exports = { LongshotFadingStrategy };","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NTSDSLmLyj6Sa7NKBVG27f","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good picture of the D004 strategy components. Let me assess what needs testing:\n\n1. **CrossPlatformArbitrageStrategy** - No unit tests. I already identified several bugs/issues:\n   - Confidence is hardcoded to `minConfidence` (0.85) regardless of spread size\n   - When `kalshiCheaper = false` (kalshi is more expensive), `targetPrice = 100 - kalshiYesPrice`, but this is the NO price, not the correct target for trading\n   - `fees * 2` calculation may be confusing\n\n2. **LongshotFadingStrategy** - No unit tests.\n   - `expectedEdge` could be 0 when `yesPrice = minPrice` (overpricingFactor = 0)\n   - Edge case: when yesPrice exactly equals minPrice or maxPrice\n\n3. **RiskManager** - Has DB dependency, hard to unit test without mocking. But the `filterSignals` fallback behavior (approve when DB is down) is a security concern I should flag.\n\nLet me now write comprehensive unit tests for `CrossPlatformArbitrageStrategy` and `LongshotFadingStrategy` since these are key D004 components with no test coverage. I'll start with the constructor defaults and work through the critical test areas.\n\nFor CrossPlatformArbitrageStrategy, I need to cover the generateSignal method thoroughly: null returns when external prices are missing or invalid, YES signals when Kalshi is cheaper, NO signals when it's more expensive, filtering by minimum spread, handling negative edges after fees, comparing across multiple platforms to find the best opportunity, and various edge cases like missing prices or IDs. I should also test batch signal generation with proper sorting by edge value and handle falsy values like zero prices correctly.\n\nFor LongshotFadingStrategy, the key tests involve validating constructor defaults, checking category filtering, enforcing price boundaries with minPrice and maxPrice thresholds, and continuing through the remaining signal generation scenarios.\n\nNow looking at the confidence and edge calculations at boundary conditions: when the price hits minPrice, the overpricing factor maxes out at 1.0, but the resulting expected edge of 0.75 still falls short of the minEdge threshold of 2, meaning no signal would ever trigger at that boundary. Similarly, at maxPrice the edge drops to zero, which also fails the minEdge check. This reveals a potential issue where the minPrice boundary is actually unreachable for generating valid signals given the current parameters. So the strategy never generates any signals at all because the edge calculation always falls short of the minimum threshold — this is a fundamental flaw that prevents the entire strategy from working. I need to write tests that expose this bug.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5450,"cache_read_input_tokens":35889,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5450,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cdc38eb2-8e84-4ba4-a86a-56104d2ecaf3","uuid":"f8a5fcee-8397-4a2b-a613-d6dbdb62c330"}
