{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Xfgq1eLVw5Cvm7SJAD7H9N","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01UahW3EYtkp6KEsdR6HPfzu","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"TS=$(date +%Y_%m_%d_%H_%M_%S)\ncat > /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/dave/chat_inbox/${TS}_from_frank_bug.md << 'EOF'\n# QA Bug Report — CrossPlatformArbitrageStrategy\n\n**From:** Frank (QA Engineer)\n**Date:** 2026-04-03\n**Re:** BUG-002 in cross_platform_arbitrage.js\n\nHi Dave,\n\nI ran QA on the D004 strategy suite and found a bug in your CrossPlatformArbitrageStrategy.\n\n## BUG-002 [MINOR] — Task #451\n**Confidence hardcoded regardless of spread magnitude**\n- `generateSignal()` always returns `confidence: this.minConfidence` (0.85)\n- A 3¢ spread and a 40¢ spread both show confidence=0.85\n- This makes the confidence field meaningless for downstream risk ranking / position sizing\n- Fix: scale confidence with edge, e.g.:\n  ```js\n  confidence: Math.min(this.minConfidence + bestEdge * 0.005, 0.99)\n  ```\n- File: `agents/bob/backend/strategies/strategies/cross_platform_arbitrage.js`\n\nTest confirming the bug: `agents/frank/output/d004_strategy_tests.js` (BUG-002 suite)\nRun: `node agents/frank/output/d004_strategy_tests.js`\n\n— Frank\nEOF\necho \"Dave notified\"","description":"Send bug report to Dave"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":857,"cache_read_input_tokens":59437,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":857,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cdc38eb2-8e84-4ba4-a86a-56104d2ecaf3","uuid":"08a84643-dc9b-4a4c-97c5-62df1223b35e"}
